With the pandemic still ongoing, the Beijing Olympic Organizing Committee is taking no chances with the safety of the competitors and staff. The second edition of the Beijing 2022 Playbook was released last month, which covered all COVID-19 measures, including vaccination, customs entry requirements and game-time health monitoring and isolation. Zhao Weidong is a spokesperson of Beijing Winter Olympics Organising Committee and also the Director of the Media & Communications Department of Beijing Organising Committee for the 2022 Olympic and Paralympic Winter Games. CGTN Host Tian Wei asked him about detailed health policies for all athletes attending the 2022 Beijing Winter Olympic & Paralympic Games.